713782f-a.text:
West 55th Street, east from but not including Eleventh Ave., showing a W.P.A. work project. Note vacant lots on either side of the street. These will form a portion of the open viaduct along the west side of Manhattan that the New York Central Railroad is constructing for their trains.
October 29, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

713781f-b.text:
West 55th Street, east from a point east of Eleventh Avenue, and across the new causeway carrying the New York Central Railroad tracks. These were removed from open streets by the co-operation of the City and the Company. See, West Side lImprovement Project.
October 24, 1939
No's. 1-2 (panaroma)
P. L. Sperr
